Rosario INTRABARTOLO, Appellant, v. The PENNSYLVANIA RAILROAD COMPANY, Appellee. No. 169. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Jan. 4, 1937. Jacob N. Geffen, of New York City (Jacquin Frank, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Ray Rood Allen, of New York City, for appellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

■ Judgment affirmed on the authority of Pennsylvania R. R. Co. v. Chamberlain, 288 U.S. 333, 53 S.Ct. 391, 77 L.Ed. 819.
